<br>
Tonight i went with a friend to collect bars etc... from the relic keep. Up until i set foot out of Sva i hadnt noticed anything like described here but as soon as i got traveling towards the keep we kept.... stopping.<br>
<br>
Stopping is the only way i can describe what happens. I asked my friend &quot;why you keep stopping see ppl ahead? lag ghosts or something?&quot;<br>
And he replies &quot;nope ive got auto run on its your run speed missing a pulse&quot;<br>
<br>
Well we ran around a bit after testing it and sure enough Roughly every 9 seconds or 6 i slow down. This is really quite laughable, You dont need high dmg you have SPEED... NOT!<br>
<br>
One thing that i have noticed is whilst inrealm the pulses pulse steady for 9 seconds or so then 3 short fast burst, then back to pulsing steady. This is only on run speed that ive seen and not on any of the other songs, while out of realm the 3 fast pulses dissapear.<br>
I wish there were an option to make demos in this game it would show perfectly this juddery sh*t we call speed song. Btw im only lvl 38 so do not have last run song.<br>
<br>
^^ please read, i have yet to experience ANY drop in speed whilst in realm. I looked at the results of your 'test' and i dont mean to sound rude but i would hardly consider them 'case closed'.<br>
<br>
Race - Rosey vs Prior from Audliten bindstone to Tomte Camp and return<br>
<br>
You only ran inrealm, and you raced against other skalds. Correct me if im rong but if all 3 run speeds were bugged then effectively you would never know even if you were getting this bug in realm. Again i dont mean to be condescending or rude but Yes there is a bug and yes it needs fixing.<br>
<br>
Also possibly the single most annoying thing that i have EVER come across (except this speed bug) is the OTHER speed bug with skalds. Omg if anyone in my team gets hit - z00p - ive lost speed. I could be safely inside a keep (as an example) and someone gets hit outside i lost my speed. This was the most annoying aspect of playing my skald in the BG's.<br>
<br>
I can testify that neither bards OR minstrel suffer from this problem. I have a lvl 50 mincer on excal and a lvl 39 bard excal (both euro servers and i have 2 accounts) and a lvl 38 skald on prywden. I can run as long as i want with either bard or minstrel so long as i personally do not engage in combat or get fired at, or meleed, even if they are misses. So this is also a bug.<br>
<br>
